    "Assuming that C is bicomplete, an 𝑛-cube is strongly cocartesian if every face is a pushout, cartesian if it is a limit diagram and cocartesian if it is a colimit diagram.A functor 𝐹: Sp 𝜔 → Sp is 𝑑-excisive if it sends strongly cocartesian (𝑑 + 1)-cubes to cartesian cubes.",
    "One should view this as a weak form of excision, i.e., a 1-excisive functor sends pushout diagrams to pullback diagrams.",
    "We will say that 𝐹 is reduced if 𝐹 ( *) ≃ *.",
    "Denote by Exc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔, Sp) the ∞-category of reduced 𝑑-excisive endofunctors of spectra 2.To any 𝐹: Sp 𝜔 → Sp, Goodwillie calculus assigns a sequence of approximations𝐹 • • • 𝑃 𝑑 𝐹 • • • 𝑃 1 𝐹 𝑃 0 𝐹 = 𝐹 ( *)in which 𝑃 𝑑 𝐹 is the universal 𝑑-excisive approximation to 𝐹.",
    "A comprehensive account of the homotopy theory of excisive functors of spectra is given in [ABHS25, §2]."
